      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <button class="faq-toggle" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          <span>Is MBBS from abroad valid in India?</span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>For India practice, foreign MBBS graduates must meet current NMC/FMGE rules and clear the applicable licensing exam such as FMGE/NExT. We review university eligibility and explain the pathway before counselling.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <button class="faq-toggle" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          <span>What is the minimum NEET score required?</span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>For most countries (Georgia, Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan), you need a qualifying NEET score — there is no minimum cutoff. Even scores around 150-200 can get you admission to good universities. For the UK, requirements are higher.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-3">
        <button class="faq-toggle" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          <span>How much does the consultancy charge?</span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Our consultancy fee is shared transparently during your first free consultation. There are no hidden charges. The fee covers university application, documentation, visa assistance, and pre-departure support. We do not charge per university — it is a single flat fee.</p>
